==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Champaign
<hw>Cham*paign"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>champaigne</ets>; same word as <ets>campagne</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
flat, open country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fair <qex>champaign</qex>, with less rivers interveined.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through Apline vale or <qex>champaign</qex> wide.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Champaign</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Champaign
<hw>Cham*paign"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Flat; open; level.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A wide, <qex>champaign</qex> country, filled with herds.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Champer</ent>⟦br⟧
